-- India's SpiceJet says fleet grounded on lack of fuel
-- By Tommy Wilkes
-- Tue Dec 16, 2014 11:54PM EST
-- None



NEW DELHI, Dec 17 (Reuters) - Indian budget carrier SpiceJet Ltd's <SPJT.BO> aircraft are currently grounded because oil companies have not refuelled any of its planes, a spokesman told Reuters on Wednesday.

Loss-making SpiceJet owes money to creditors including oil companies.  On Tuesday, the civil aviation ministry said airport operators would be asked to give the airline 15 days to make payments, while state oil companies would be ask to give credit for up to 15 days. [ID:nL3N0U02UO]